messages.message: Ok this is supppeerrrr strange, Chrome allows you to bypass unsafe screens by typing `badidea` and it will allow you through, but for some reason navigating to github causes me to get redirected to instabase.com (http://instabase.com)?
So it looks like something on my computer causes `http://githubrawusercontent.com/` to redirect to localhost…
I’m restarting my computer for the first time in months maybe that will help :joy:
Lmao, google really makes you type "badidea" if you want to move forward anyways??
Lol yes :joy: so sometimes they give you the “proceed anyways” button. But if they dont, you can *still* bypass it by just typing “badidea” or “thisisunsafe” which is kinda hilarious
This is amazing and sad at the same time :joy:
omg i needed that like a day ago lol. had to  use safari
My issue is that not even my terminal cann access the site so I think something weird is happening with my dns or proxy settings
btw i can’t access http://githubrawusercontent.com/ at all. it just says it can’t be reached
I think you need to access a specific resource
oh yeah haha apparently it’s raw.githubusercontent.com (http://raw.githubusercontent.com) and not githubrawusercontent.com (http://githubrawusercontent.com)
it would be great if we could redirect everyone’s githubusercontent to instabase :wink:
neither works haha, I mean the issue is that spacy download uses that file, and so in my terminal spacy download fails because it cant load that link
